---
import { toolCount, transportModes } from "../data/setup";

const hevyApiKeyUrl = "https://hevy.com/settings?developer";
const connectionPrompt = "Which Hevy account is connected?";
---

<section class="setup-section section" id="setup" aria-labelledby="setup-title">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="section-heading section-heading--split">
			<div>
				<p class="context-line">Setup</p>
				<h2 id="setup-title">Connect Hevy.<br />Ask your first question.</h2>
			</div>
			<p>
				Start with browser sign-in for the shortest path to all {toolCount} tools. Prefer a fixed API key
				or local control? Direct HTTPS and local mode are available.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="setup" data-setup>
			<div class="transport-intro">
				<p>
					<strong>Choose how your assistant connects.</strong> You can switch methods without losing
					the instructions below.
				</p>
				<p>
					Browser sign-in is recommended for most people. Use direct HTTPS when your client accepts a
					fixed API key, or local mode when you want the process on your machine.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="transport-switcher" role="tablist" aria-label="Connection mode">
				{transportModes.map((mode, index) => (
					<button
						type="button"
						role="tab"
						aria-selected={index === 0 ? "true" : "false"}
						aria-controls={`setup-${mode.id}`}
						id={`setup-tab-${mode.id}`}
						tabindex={index === 0 ? 0 : -1}
						data-transport-tab={mode.id}
					>
						<span class="transport-switcher__label">
							<strong>{mode.label}</strong>
							<small>{mode.audience}</small>
						</span>
						{mode.badge && <span class="recommendation">{mode.badge}</span>}
					</button>
				))}
			</div>

			<div class="setup-shared setup-panel__intro">
				<div class="setup-panel__number">01</div>
				<div>
					<h3>Get and verify your Hevy API key</h3>
					<p>
						Create a Hevy API key and keep it handy. Browser sign-in asks for it once and stores it
						encrypted in your OAuth grant; direct HTTPS sends it as a bearer credential; local mode
						passes it through your client's environment.
					</p>
					<div class="key-actions">
						<a
							class="button button--outline button--small"
							href={hevyApiKeyUrl}
							target="_blank"
							rel="noreferrer"
						>
							Open Hevy API settings <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
						</a>
						<span>Hevy PRO is required for API access.</span>
					</div>
					<div class="key-check" data-key-check>
						<div class="key-check__heading">
							<strong>Check the key before configuring your client</strong>
							<span>This makes a read-only account request directly to Hevy.</span>
						</div>
						<form data-key-check-form>
							<label class="sr-only" for="hevy-api-key">Hevy API key</label>
							<input
								id="hevy-api-key"
								type="password"
								name="hevy-api-key"
								placeholder="Paste your Hevy API key"
								autocomplete="off"
								autocapitalize="none"
								spellcheck="false"
								required
							/>
							<button
								class="button button--ink button--small"
								type="submit"
								data-key-check-button
							>
								Check key
							</button>
						</form>
						<p class="key-check__privacy">
							For this check only, your browser sends the key directly to Hevy. This site never
							receives or stores it.
						</p>
						<p
							class="key-check__status"
							role="status"
							aria-live="polite"
							aria-atomic="true"
							data-key-check-status
						></p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			{transportModes.map((mode) => (
				<div
					class="setup-panel"
					id={`setup-${mode.id}`}
					role="tabpanel"
					aria-labelledby={`setup-tab-${mode.id}`}
					data-transport-panel={mode.id}
				>
					<div class="setup-panel__workspace" data-client-tabs>
						<div class="setup-panel__guide">
							<div class="setup-panel__number">02</div>
							<div>
								<h3>Choose your AI assistant</h3>
								<p>{mode.description}</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="client-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label={`${mode.label} clients`}>
							{mode.clients.map((client, clientIndex) => (
								<button
									type="button"
									role="tab"
									aria-selected={clientIndex === 0 ? "true" : "false"}
									aria-controls={`${mode.id}-${client.id}-panel`}
									id={`${mode.id}-${client.id}-tab`}
									tabindex={clientIndex === 0 ? 0 : -1}
									data-client-tab={client.id}
								>
									{client.label}
								</button>
							))}
						</div>

						{mode.clients.map((client) => (
							<div
								class="client-panel"
								id={`${mode.id}-${client.id}-panel`}
								role="tabpanel"
								aria-labelledby={`${mode.id}-${client.id}-tab`}
								data-client-panel={client.id}
							>
								<div class="code-panel">
									<div class="code-panel__bar">
										<span>{client.format}</span>
										<button
											type="button"
											aria-describedby={`${mode.id}-${client.id}-copy-status`}
											data-copy-button
											data-copy-value={client.code}
										>
											<span data-copy-label>Copy</span>
										</button>
									</div>
									<pre tabindex="0" data-copy-target><code>{client.code}</code></pre>
								</div>
								<p
									class="copy-status"
									id={`${mode.id}-${client.id}-copy-status`}
									aria-live="polite"
									aria-atomic="true"
									data-copy-status
								></p>
								{client.code.includes("your-hevy-api-key") && (
									<p class="credential-note">
										<strong>Before you save:</strong> replace <code>your-hevy-api-key</code> and never
										commit or screenshot the real value.
									</p>
								)}
								<p class="verification">
									<span>{client.verificationLabel ?? "After saving"}</span>{client.verification}
								</p>
							</div>
						))}
					</div>
				</div>
			))}

			<div class="setup-shared setup-panel__finish">
				<div class="setup-panel__number">03</div>
				<div>
					<h3>Ask your first question</h3>
					<p>After reconnecting your client, start with this read-only question:</p>
					<div class="connection-prompt">
						<blockquote tabindex="0" data-copy-target>“{connectionPrompt}”</blockquote>
						<button
							type="button"
							aria-describedby="prompt-copy-status"
							data-copy-button
							data-copy-value={connectionPrompt}
						>
							<span data-copy-label>Copy question</span>
						</button>
					</div>
					<p
						class="copy-status"
						id="prompt-copy-status"
						aria-live="polite"
						aria-atomic="true"
						data-copy-status
					></p>
					<p class="connection-prompt__success">
						If your assistant returns your Hevy profile, the connection is working. Then try:
						“Give me a training summary for the last four weeks.”
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<details class="more-options">
				<summary>More setup options</summary>
				<div class="more-options__content">
					<div>
						<h3>Run with Bun or Docker</h3>
						<p>Run the local server with bunx or the official multi-architecture Docker image.</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<h3>Understand OAuth security</h3>
						<p>
							The key check goes directly from your browser to Hevy. Browser sign-in stores the
							validated key encrypted inside the OAuth grant; rotating the key invalidates that grant.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<h3>Troubleshoot a connection</h3>
						<p>Find client configuration locations, key checks, and exact recovery steps in the README.</p>
					</div>
					<a class="text-link" href="https://github.com/chrisdoc/hevy-mcp#quick-start">
						Read the complete setup guide <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
					</a>
				</div>
			</details>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<script>
	import { initializeSetupGuide } from "../scripts/setup-guide";

	initializeSetupGuide();
</script>
